race.description: Newcastle Car & Truck Super Mdn Plate
race.comment: CHISHOLM (7) is a regally bred filly resuming for the Price/Kent stable. Raced once last prep and found the smart Esha too good over 1000m in Adelaide. Victorian visitor who has bumped into a smart field here, but the daughter of I Am Invincible and Snitzerland can deliver. SWORDPLAY (10) last appeared on debut five months ago when she led for home over 1100m at Warwick Farm but folded. Started favourite that day so plenty was expected. Trialling in great style and looks the obvious threat. APOLLO RIDGE (1) returns from a 169-day break. Led and just failed to hold on when resuming over 1000m at Wyong last prep. Might run a cheeky race over this sharp journey. COOL BLAZE (3) battled on fairly for fourth in a similar maiden here a fortnight ago. Can find the frame again at the third run back. MISTY VEIL (9) finished third as favourite here at this trip at her only appearance back in June. Recent trial winner who cannot be underestimated.
